Articles.Content:
CSA Contares 'KHI' offer a small set of CNSA/Chinese launcher and spaceships.

 

Reference diameters are 0.3125m, 0.625m, 0.9375m, 1.25m, 1.5m, 1.875m, 2.2m (ESA Parts only), 2.5m, 3.75m and 5.0m.
Inquiries regarding diameters are superfluous by the effort of simple head calculations or a calculator.

 

Required mods:

Download via SpaceDock

Craft-Files included!

Versions / Update

Quote

2.0.0 initial
2.0.1 add missing parts, add missing realPlume settings, more craft files
2.0.2 update to 1.4.1. Change RCS effects
2.0.3 update SAS modules. Add missing RealPlume effects on LH2/LOX engines
2.0.4 update cfg files. Add more missing RealPlume settings
2.0.5 adds some parts (Tanks and engines) to build replicas of CZ-3 series. Rework of CZ-2/3 second stage engine.
2.0.6 adds some parts to build the LUNA SPACE SHIP.
2.0.7 adds bigger 2nd stage for KHI-5 (CZ-5). Finish the CRV. Some finetuning
2.0.8 update to KSP 1.8.1
2.0.9 changelog on GitHub
2.0.11 compatibility update

@Wildcat111 if you load the newest CORE all will work well.

Thanks! However, there is another slight problem. The CZ-2E/F's first stage is burning out faster than the boosters, instead of burning longer.

3 minutes ago, Wildcat111 said:

Thanks! However, there is another slight problem. The CZ-2E/F's first stage is burning out faster than the boosters, instead of burning longer.

That's right. Please reduce the LFO in the booster by 10%.  The time between booster separation and burn out of 1st stage is ~ 3 seconds (in real).
Ok, thanks!
@hraban is there any RSS/RO configs to this mod. I'm trying to find a Chinese rocket mod , but there are none at the moment.
RSS/RO = NO
Excellent!
Wa, useful mod, thank you, and whether it is considered for it plus a realistic painting

With the new update you can also build the CZ-4 series launcher:

Edited October 23, 2018 by hraban
@hraban I downloaded all dependancies, but the Shenzhou craft file is apparently missing parts.

8 hours ago, sslaptnhablhat said:

@hraban I downloaded all dependancies, but the Shenzhou craft file is apparently missing parts.

Excuse me, but there is currently no time to update the craft files. Regarding the Shenzhou I assume that the decoupler between the orbital module and the return capsule is missing, which comes from the submod CSA RUS.

Including a good portion of "creative freedoms", a model was created based on the little information about the planned Chinese spaceship, which will be published as part of the update to the current KSP version 1.6. Further information is available under the attached link.

Details from N. Brügge (www.b14643.de)

First ingame screenshot from Crew Transport System (CTS)

- Commad Module (Capsule) holds up to 5 Khibonauts with integrated RCS-System, Light and TAC-LS supplies for 24 days.
- Placeholder IVA
- droppable heatshield
- Decoupler with service line
- Service Module with integrated radiators, RCS backup engines and 4 main rocket engines, integrated TAC-LS (Carbon Extractor and Water Purifier). Also integrated a monoprop fuel cell.

With parachutes, docking port, solar panels and com-dish round about 14 tonns. Ready to launch with KHI-5 (CZ-5) with 2 boosters for kerbal orbital missions.
GitHub (see OP) is updated. Small set of Craft-Files are included. There is no official update to 1.6.x but i hope you will give me response to finish the work for update.
New Craft-Files via GitHub (link in OP)
